title: Avoid NullPointerException onDestroy
message:
Avoid NullPointerException onDestroy

Check that locationManager is not null before trying to
remove location listener updates so that it won't throw a
NullPointerException.

title: Determine location on connectivity changes. It is probable that a connectivity
message:
Determine location on connectivity changes. It is probable that a connectivity
change indicates a location change.

title: CM Privacy Guard workaround: try to register for location updates
message:
CM Privacy Guard workaround: try to register for location updates
as soon as the option is set so that it asks for permission.

title: Change shouldUpdate method in MainActivity:
message:
Change shouldUpdate method in MainActivity:

On every background location update, check if it is different from the previuos location
and store this in a SharedPreference boolean ('cityChanged'). Check it onResume in
MainActivity to show the current location. Like this, we can avoid checking the location
on every onResume (which is time-consuming and annoying).

title: Merge pull request #99 from SpiritCroc/updateThreshold
message:
Merge pull request #99 from SpiritCroc/updateThreshold

Restrict automatic weather updates on resume

title: Restrict automatic weather updates on resume
message:
Restrict automatic weather updates on resume

Only update if last check is longer ago than a specified threshold (currently 5 minutes).

It can be annoying that weather is always reloaded on main activity resume, even if the activity was only away for a few seconds (e.g. after changing some settings); and also consume mobile data more than necessary, as weather won't change every few minutes. Users can still manually reload if necessary.

title: Merge pull request #96 from SpiritCroc/widget
message:
Merge pull request #96 from SpiritCroc/widget

Use alarm service to update time widget; widget preview images

title: Remove redundant update schedule, already called onUpdate
message: Remove redundant update schedule, already called onUpdate

title: Use the android alarm service to update time widget
message:
Use the android alarm service to update time widget

The previous solution was bad because of the following aspects:
- Extending the Application class is not recommended, as it often is not required, like in this case
- The android system is allowed to remove apps to save memory and battery. Once done, the widget won't update the time anymore until the application is re-opened by the user (or possibly our background weather service)
- Furthermore, the handler kept the application alive, consuming more battery than required, especially if actually no time widget is used by the user

Instead, using an alarm receiver to schedule updates to an app that might not be running all the time is the recommended way
